      skos:broader narr:OperatingModelShifts ;
      skos:note "a demo-call prospect does direct sales (face-to-face with executives, needs pre-read and demo materials); Tony does influence sales (warm intros, one-sheet as leave-behind). Explicit division of labor: opening doors vs. providing depth. a demo-call prospect is active and giving direct feedback; Tony is playing it by ear on deeper involvement." ;
      narr:theme "Two-track sales motion: influence sales (Tony) and direct sales (a demo-call prospect) require different materials and engagement models" .

